Legendary Madonna has officially named Fireboy DML as the artiste that would be featured on the remix of her classic song ‘Frozen.’ Pictures of the two musical acts surfaced online and even though most people knew it they were shoots from on-set the ‘Frozen’ remix; it was however uncertain if the YBNL artiste featured on it. Putting paid to every doubt, the 63-year-old Michigan-born music icon took to her Instagram page on Tuesday to share photos with Fireboy DML while confirming their collaboration. The “Queen of Pop” revealed the “Peru” crooner will feature in the song and video of “Frozen” remix alongside its release date. Madonna wrote: “Frozen Remix song and video featuring @fireboydml. Music drops March 3rd………. Video soon after! #frozen.”   I’m fine with being called ‘Ade Tiger’ – Titi Kuti     15th Headies holds in Atlanta, Bentley for next rated act     Reactions over Fireboy DML’s picture with Madonna   “Frozen” is a song by the American singer from her seventh studio album “Ray of Light” (1998). It was released as the lead single from the album on February 23, 1998 by Maverick and Warner Bro. Records. “Frozen” received acclaim from music critics, some of whom deemed it an album standout. It was described as being a masterpiece, and its melodic beat and sound were defined as “cinematic”. The single was also a worldwide commercial success. It became Madonna’s sixth single to peak at number two on the US Billboard Hot 100, making her the artist with the most number-two hits in the history of that chart. “Frozen” also became her first single to debut at the top of the UK Singles Chart, while reaching number one in Finland, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Scotland and Spain and the top five elsewhere.